## Dashboard 1: ISSO Operational Dashboard

**Audience:** ISSO
**Frequency:** Daily review (high-level scan); Weekly detailed review; Monthly full update
**Purpose:** Comprehensive operational visibility — everything the ISSO needs to manage the continuous monitoring program

**Design principles:**

The ISSO dashboard is the source of truth for the security program's current state. It should be complete rather than curated — the ISSO needs to see every indicator, including the ones that are Yellow or Red, without any filtering or aggregation that obscures operational detail.

**Layout — Five panels, one per control domain:**

---

*Panel 1 — Vulnerability Management*

Patch SLA Compliance Rate (KPI-VM-1):
- Monthly bar chart: 12 months of SLA compliance rate. Bar color: Green (≥95%), Yellow (90-94%), Red (<90%). Current month highlighted.
- Current month value displayed prominently: [e.g.] "October: 97% — GREEN ✓"

High Vulnerability Aging Counter (KRI-VM-1):
- Simple counter displayed prominently: "High vulnerabilities beyond 30-day SLA: [N]"
- Zero = Green text. 1-2 with POA&M = Yellow. 3+ or any without POA&M = Red.
- If non-zero: List of specific findings with finding ID, severity, days beyond SLA, POA&M item reference.

---

*Panel 2 — Access Control*

Access Review Completion Rate (KPI-AC-1a):
- Last 4 quarters: "Q1: Completed Day 8/10 ✓ | Q2: Completed Day [X]/10 | Q3: TBD | Q4: TBD"
- Simple pass/fail per quarter with completion day noted.

Access Review Accuracy Rate (KPI-AC-1b):
- Last 4 quarters: Number of corrections required per review. Trend arrow (improving/stable/degrading).
- "Q1: 1 correction (M-004 — role reassignment) | Q2: [N] corrections"

Privileged Account Dormancy (KRI-AC-1):
- "Days since last IT Administrator login: [N] | Days since last ISSO login: [N]"
- Both under 30 days = Green. Either at/beyond 30 days = immediate action flag.

---

*Panel 3 — Contingency Planning*

Backup Success Rate (KPI-CP-1a):
- Monthly backup job completion rate: "October: 100% (30/30 scheduled jobs completed) — GREEN ✓"
- Any month with missed backup jobs highlighted in red with the specific missed job identified.

RTO Compliance and Margin Trend (KPI-CP-1b + KRI-CP-1):
- Line chart: Quarterly restoration test completion times over the authorization period.
- Horizontal reference lines: RTO target (4 hours = 240 minutes) in red, Yellow threshold (180 minutes, 60-minute margin) in yellow.
- Q1 data point: 227 minutes. Trend direction arrow. Current margin value: "RTO Margin: 13 minutes — YELLOW ⚠"
- This visualization immediately communicates the concern from M-003: the line is rising toward the Red reference line.

---

*Panel 4 — Incident Response*

MTTC Trend (KPI-IR-1):
- If live incident data exists: scatter plot of Tier 3 incidents with containment time. If no live incidents: "No Tier 3 incidents this quarter — tabletop exercise MTTC: [N] minutes"
- Target reference line: 30 minutes.

IR Tabletop Exercise Recency (KRI-IR-1):
- Simple elapsed time counter: "Days since last documented tabletop exercise: [N]"
- Color coded against the 365-day threshold.

---

*Panel 5 — Security Awareness Training*

Training Completion Currency (KPI-AT-1):
- "Active users with training current (within 12 months): [N]/[Total] — [%]"
- Users with training expiring in the next 30 days: [N] (advance warning)

Phishing Simulation Click Rate (KRI-AT-1):
- If simulation program implemented: most recent click rate with trend.
- If not yet implemented: "⚠ Phishing simulation program not yet implemented — effectiveness metric absent. See Day 79 improvement proposal."

This last entry — explicitly calling out that the effectiveness metric is absent — is the honest dashboard design principle in action. Hiding the absence of an effectiveness metric because the simulation program has not been built yet would produce a misleading all-green training panel. Displaying the gap maintains the dashboard's integrity as a genuine governance tool.

