## Dashboard 2: Health IT Manager Monthly Summary

**Audience:** Health IT Manager (System Owner)
**Frequency:** Monthly (included in the monthly monitoring summary report)
**Purpose:** Surface the metrics that require Health IT Manager awareness or action; avoid overwhelming a non-security-specialist with technical detail

**Design principle:** The Health IT Manager's dashboard answers exactly three questions: Is anything wrong right now? Are my POA&M items on track? What is coming up that requires my attention?

**Layout — Three sections:**

*Section 1 — Current Status (traffic light summary):*

| Metric | Status | Note |
|---|---|---|
| Access review (Q2 due date) | 🟡 Yellow | Due in 12 days |
| Backup restoration RTO | 🟡 Yellow | 13-min margin — optimization in progress |
| CP-2 downtime procedures | 🟡 Yellow | 12 days to 90-day condition deadline |
| Training completion | 🟢 Green | 100% current |
| Vulnerability patching | 🟢 Green | 97% SLA compliance |

This is the complete picture the Health IT Manager needs for their monthly awareness. Five rows, five traffic lights, brief notes. Reading time: under 60 seconds.

*Section 2 — My POA&M Items:*

The Health IT Manager is the owner of POA&M items 001 (CP-2), M-004 (role change notification), and the co-owner of several training items. This section lists only those items:

| Item | Status | Days to Deadline | Action Required |
|---|---|---|---|
| 001 — CP-2 Clinical downtime | In progress | 12 | Milestone 3 meeting confirmation needed — see ISSO note |
| M-004 — Role change notification | In progress | 33 | Draft HR process update for ISSO review |

*Section 3 — Upcoming (next 30 days):*
- Q2 quarterly access review: Due [specific date — 12 days]
- AO 45-day CP-2 check-in: [date — this week]
- CP-4 alternate site test: [date — 18 days]

The Health IT Manager monthly summary does not include CVSS scores, CloudTrail log summaries, or Config compliance details. Those are ISSO operational data. The Health IT Manager needs to know what requires their action and what is coming — not the full technical picture.

