## Dashboard 3: AO Quarterly Report — Visual Summary Page

**Audience:** Executive Director (Authorizing Official)
**Frequency:** Quarterly (the first page of the quarterly POA&M status report)
**Purpose:** Enable the AO to assess authorization status in under two minutes, with navigation to detail for any indicator requiring deeper review

**Design principle:** The AO's one-page visual summary is the executive distillation of the entire security program's quarterly performance. It should be printable, readable without security expertise, and immediately actionable — the AO should be able to read it and know exactly what decisions, if any, they need to make.

**Layout — Three sections on one page:**

*Section 1 — Authorization Condition Status (most prominent):*

Displayed as four condition boxes, each with a large status indicator:
```
┌─────────────────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│  Condition 1: CP-2 Downtime     │  │  Condition 2: Quarterly Reporting│
│  ⚠ AT RISK — 12 days remaining  │  │  ✓ MET — This report             │
│  Action required — see p.2      │  │                                  │
└─────────────────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────────┘
┌─────────────────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│  Condition 3: Material Risk     │  │  Condition 4: Annual CM Review   │
│  ✓ MET — No reportable events   │  │  ◷ DUE [auth date + 1 year]     │
│                                  │  │  Not yet required                │
└─────────────────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────────┘
```

The AT RISK box for Condition 1 is visually prominent — larger border, yellow background. The AO's eye goes there immediately. The bottom text "Action required — see p.2" tells the AO exactly where to find the detail.

*Section 2 — Security Program Health (five headline metrics):*

Simple gauge-style indicators with a one-line explanation:

- **Patch SLA Compliance:** 97% 🟢 — Critical/High vulnerabilities patched within required timeframe
- **RTO Margin:** 13 minutes 🟡 — Backup restoration within RTO target but margin narrowing; optimization in progress
- **Access Review Accuracy:** 1 correction Q1 🟢 — Over-privileged role identified and corrected immediately
- **Training Completion:** 100% 🟢 — All active users current within 12 months
- **Vulnerability Aging:** 0 findings beyond SLA 🟢 — No unaddressed High findings

*Section 3 — POA&M Summary (three numbers):*
```
Items Closed This Quarter: 5
Items Opened This Quarter: 2  
Items Currently Open: 7 (1 Moderate, 6 Low)
```

One sentence below: "No findings above Moderate severity. One Moderate item (CP-2 Condition — AT RISK) requires AO engagement this week. See p.2 for detail."

---

The AO reads this page and knows: one condition is at risk and requires their attention, the security program is otherwise performing well, and the detail they need is on page 2. Reading time under 90 seconds. Decision clarity immediate.

